  "desc": "EA SPORTS FC 26 version 1.5.3 is dropping soon for all platforms and includes the updates below.\n\n**Gameplay**\n\nAddressed the following issues:\n\n- Goalkeepers will now kick the ball out of play if a player excessively wastes time by passing back to them over and over again.\n  - This change is to address rare scenarios that are inauthentic to football and does not impact a typical backpass.\n\n**Ultimate Team**\n\nAddressed the following issues:\n\n- Some kits and badges were not searchable in the transfer market.\n- Some Player Celebration animation previews did not display when selected.\n\n**Career Mode**\n\nMade the following changes:\n\n- Added a missing separator in European competition standings, making it easier to see which teams advance to playoffs.\n- In Career Mode, when applying for a job, it now automatically adds the team to your watchlist.\n- Added labels next to team crests in challenge descriptions to clearly differentiate men's and women's teams.\n- Added a clearer description on the challenge completion UI to explain how saves and career progress work after completion.\n- Managers with low job security at season's end are now upgraded to Okay.\n\nAddressed the following issues:\n\n- Sometimes, Managers were incorrectly assigned to a different team when selecting Icons & Heroes in career creation.\n- In the Manager Career, ICON players could have requested low wages during contract negotiations.\n- In some cases, a League-winning team was placed in the incorrect European League.\n- Addressed instances of incorrect or overlapping text.\n\n**General, Audio, and Visual**\n\nMade the following changes:\n\n- Updated some names, overlays, kits, sponsors,  crests, banners, scarves, flags, logos, hair, boots, star heads, ad boards.\n\nAddressed the following issues:\n\n- Addressed various stability issues that could have occurred.\n\n‌\n\nWant to provide us direct feedback about EA SPORTS FC 26? [https://go.ea.com/fc26pfp](https://go.ea.com/fc26pfp \"‌\") and let us know what you think, it only takes a few minutes.\n\nThanks to those who’ve provided and continue to provide feedback. Throughout the course of the EA SPORTS FC 26 season, we'll provide you with more information and updates if and when they become available. Be sure to follow \\@‌EASFCDIRECT on X as well as WhatsApp, and check out the EA SPORTS FC Tracker for the latest news and updates.\n\n- The EA SPORTS FC Team",
